# Sentinel-IoT MQTT ACL — per-tenant topic isolation.
#
# Topic namespace (multi-tenant SaaS):
#   tenants/<slug>/iot/<building>/<room>/<device_id>/telemetry
#   tenants/<slug>/iot/<building>/<room>/<device_id>/event
#   tenants/<slug>/security/#         (ingestor-written security events)
#
# A device principal authenticates with an MQTT username equal to its tenant
# slug (provisioned by `php artisan tenant:provision`). The `pattern` rules
# below use Mosquitto's %u substitution so each device user can only publish
# under its OWN tenant prefix — a leaked credential for tenant "acme" can never
# write into "globex".

# --- Per-tenant device principals (username == tenant slug) ------------------
# Devices may ONLY publish telemetry/events within their tenant namespace.
pattern write tenants/%u/iot/#

# --- Central ingestor --------------------------------------------------------
# The ingestor is the single trusted consumer. It reads every tenant's IoT and
# security topics and writes derived security events back.
user sentinel_ingestor
topic read tenants/+/iot/#
topic read tenants/+/security/#
topic write tenants/+/security/#
# Legacy flat namespace (single-tenant demo / backward compatibility).
topic read iot/#
topic read security/#
topic write security/#

# --- Legacy single-tenant device principal (demo seed only) ------------------
# Kept so the existing DemoSeeder + attack-simulator continue to work against
# the flat `iot/#` namespace. Do NOT issue this credential to real clients in a
# multi-tenant deployment; use per-tenant principals above.
user sentinel_device
topic write iot/#
